ing the static block of DefaultCredentialsProviderTest to use a shared helper. I could also think about adding a helper directly in AppEngineCredentialsTest to avoid dependencies. \\n\\nI can also explore if including a nested helper would work, ensuring everything is organized without extra top-level classes.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test initialization**\\n\\nI’m thinking about adding a static block in DefaultCredentialsProviderTest that calls AppEngineCredentialsTest.installAppIdentityServiceFactory(). This way, I can ensure static initialization occurs before the Default test runs. If Default runs first, it calls register; if AppEngine runs first, it does that too.\\n\\nI need to handle potential duplicates because if they register with the same base, it overrides without issues. Once the runtime registry is initialized after invoking GoogleCredentials.getAppDefault, subsequent registers will throw an IllegalStateException. So, I’ll ensure the install method catches that exception.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering static block setup**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to set up the static block in our tests before using methods, which feels like a good plan. It seems we don’t need direct reflection here, which is a relief. I’m also considering whether we should use ServiceLoader for Native Image. There’s something about direct registration and RuntimeRegistry with ServiceFactoryFactory—I think that should work with our provider, especially since we’re avoiding dynamic class loading. This approach seems promising!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking user credentials**\\n\\nI’m considering if another test loads user credentials earlier. It feels important to verify that the tests are functioning correctly. So, I’ll check other tests to ensure everything is working as it should, especially to avoid any issues down the line. It’s all about making sure the process runs smoothly and efficiently, right? I just want to keep everything organized and clear, so the best approach is to double-check.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_zAnhP1lEBrbgCJzuikUBOQya|fc_0cb3d34974fed614016a2a92b71e0c81979b4b46bf881a0e37", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.auth/google-auth-library-oauth2-http/1.48.0/src/test/java/com_google_auth/google_auth_library_oauth2_http/ClientIdTest.java", "limit": 220}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_u5WY0gG7ri0Mfy3MMUVeH0Va|fc_0cb3d34974fed614016a2a92b71e2081978365afb94414b365", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.auth/google-auth-library-oauth2-http/1.48.0/src/test/java/com_google_auth/google_auth_library_oauth2_http/OAuth2CredentialsTest.java", "limit": 220}}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_YvhHKwQpBKnoege0Ls5REPUk|fc_0cb3d34974fed614016a2a92b71e2c819783d2e8f1a972863c", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.google.auth/google-auth-library-oauth2-http/1.48.0/src/test/java/com_google_auth/google_auth_library_oauth2_http/IdTokenTest.java", "limit": 220}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3080, "output": 1458, "cacheRead": 30208, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34746, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781174938601, "responseId": "resp_0cb3d34974fed614016a2a929b20a08197a71b1d7a5d2dfdac"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_zAnhP1lEBrbgCJzuikUBOQya|fc_0cb3d34974fed614016a2a92b71e0c81979b4b46bf881a0e37", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_google_auth.google_auth_library_oauth2_http;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.google.auth.oauth2.ClientId;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class ClientIdTest {\n    @Test\n    public void fromResourceLoadsClientIdJsonLocatedRelativeToCaller() throws IOException {\n        ClientId clientId = ClientId.fromResource(ClientIdTest.class, \"client_id.json\");\n\n        assertThat(clientId.getClientId()).isEqualTo(\"test-client-id.apps.googleusercontent.com\");\n        assertThat(clientId.getClientSecret()).isEqualTo(\"test-client-secret\");\n\n        ClientId rotatedClientId = clientId.toBuilder()\n                .setClientSecret(\"rotated-client-secret\")\n                .build();\n        assertThat(rotatedClientId.getClientId()).isEqualTo(clientId.getClientId());\n        assertThat(rotatedClientId.getClientSecret()).isEqualTo(\"rotated-client-secret\");\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781174967849}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_u5WY0gG7ri0Mfy3MMUVeH0Va|fc_0cb3d34974fed614016a2a92b71e2081978365afb94414b365", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_google_auth.google_auth_library_oauth2_http;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.google.auth.http.AuthHttpConstants;\nimport com.google.auth.oauth2.AccessToken;\nimport com.google.auth.oauth2.UserCredentials;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.net.URI;\nimport java.util.Date;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class OAuth2CredentialsTest {\n    private static final URI AUDIENCE_URI = URI.create(\"https://example.test/resource\");\n\n    @Test\n    public void userCredentialsDeserializationRestoresDefaultTransportFactory() throws Exception {\n        AccessToken accessToken = new AccessToken(\n                \"access-token\",\n                new Date(System.currentTimeMillis() + 3_600_000));\n        UserCredentials credentials = UserCredentials.newBuilder()\n                .setClientId(\"client-id\")\n                .setClientSecret(\"client-secret\")\n                .setAccessToken(accessToken)\n                .setQuotaProjectId(\"quota-project\")\n                .build();\n\n        UserCredentials restored;\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new ObjectInputStream(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(serialize(credentials)))) {\n            restored = (UserCredentials) input.readObject();\n        }\n\n        Map<String, List<String>> requestMetadata = restored.getRequestMetadata(AUDIENCE_URI);\n        assertThat(requestMetadata)\n                .containsEntry(AuthHttpConstants.AUTHORIZATION, List.of(\"Bearer access-token\"));\n        assertThat(restored).isEqualTo(credentials);\n        assertThat(restored.toString()).contains(\"client-id\", \"quota-project\");\n    }\n\n    private static byte[] serialize(UserCredentials credentials) throws Exception {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            output.writeObject(credentials);\n        }\n        return bytes.toByteArray();\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781174967852}, {"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_YvhHKwQpBKnoege0Ls5REPUk|fc_0cb3d34974fed614016a2a92b71e2c819783d2e8f1a972863c", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_google_auth.google_auth_library_oauth2_http;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.google.auth.oauth2.IdToken;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.util.Base64;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class IdTokenTest {\n    @Test\n    public void serializationRoundTripRestoresParsedJsonWebSignature() throws Exception {\n        String tokenValue = createUnsignedJwt();\n        IdToken token = IdToken.create(tokenValue);\n\n        ByteArrayOutputStream bytes = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream output = new ObjectOutputStream(bytes)) {\n            output.writeObject(token);\n        }\n\n        IdToken restored;\n        try (ObjectInputStream input = new ObjectInputStream(\n                new ByteArrayInputStream(bytes.toByteArray()))) {\n            restored = (IdToken) input.readObject();\n        }\n\n        assertThat(restored.getTokenValue()).isEqualTo(tokenValue);\n        assertThat(restored).isEqualTo(token);\n        assertThat(restored.hashCode()).isEqualTo(token.hashCode());\n        assertThat(restored.toString()).contains(tokenValue);\n    }\n\n    private static String createUnsignedJwt() {\n        String header = \"\"\"\n                {\"alg\":\"none\",\"typ\":\"JWT\"}\n                \"\"\";\n        String payload = \"\"\"\n                {\"iss\":\"https://accounts.google.com\",\"sub\":\"subject\",\"aud\":\"audience\",\"exp\":2524608000}\n                \"\"\";\n        return encode(header) + \".\" + encode(payload) + \".\";\n    }\n\n    private static String encode(String value) {\n        return Base64.getUrlEncoder()\n                .withoutPadding()\n                .encodeToString(value.getBytes(StandardCharsets.UTF_8));\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781174967852}]}
